---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro"
---

<Layout
  title="Research Network - Ioannis Lamprou"
  description="Research collaborations and academic network of Ioannis (John) Lamprou, AI researcher at Technical University of Crete"
>
  <main class="px-4 max-w-4xl mx-auto py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Research Network & Collaborations</h1>
    
    <section class="space-y-8">
      
      <!-- Academic Affiliations -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Academic Affiliations</h2>
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <p><strong>Ioannis Lamprou</strong> is affiliated with:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-1">
            <li><a href="https://www.tuc.gr" class="text-blue-600">Technical University of Crete (TUC)</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://parasecurity.edu.gr" class="text-blue-600">Parasecurity Group</a></li>
            <li>Telecommunication Systems Research Institute (T.S.I.)</li>
            <li>Institute of Computer Science, FORTH (ICS-FORTH)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Research Areas -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Research Domains</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-medium mb-2">Artificial Intelligence</h3>
            <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
              <li>• Large Language Models (LLMs)</li>
              <li>• Natural Language Processing</li>
              <li>• Machine Learning</li>
              <li>• Deep Learning</li>
              <li>• Neural Networks</li>
              <li>• Mixture-of-Experts architectures</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-medium mb-2">Applications</h3>
            <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
              <li>• Social Media Analysis</li>
              <li>• Bot Detection</li>
              <li>• Cybersecurity</li>
              <li>• Sentiment Analysis</li>
              <li>• Malicious Code Detection</li>
              <li>• Crisis Communication</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Geographic Context -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Location & Context</h2>
        <p>Based in <strong>Greece</strong>, Ioannis Lamprou contributes to the European AI research landscape through his work at one of Greece's leading technical universities. His research bridges theoretical AI advances with practical cybersecurity applications, contributing to both academic knowledge and real-world security solutions.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Research Impact -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Publications & Impact</h2>
        <p>Research contributions include peer-reviewed publications on:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-1">
          <li><strong>Russo-Ukrainian War social media analysis</strong> - Understanding information warfare patterns</li>
          <li><strong>Twitter bot detection using machine learning</strong> - Advanced algorithms for automated account identification</li>
          <li><strong>Crisis communication patterns</strong> - How social media shapes public discourse during conflicts</li>
          <li><strong>Political sentiment analysis</strong> - Real-time analysis of electoral sentiment in Greece</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Current Research -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Current Research Focus</h2>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-medium mb-3">Active Projects</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
            <li><strong>MSc Thesis:</strong> Retentive Networks for malicious code detection</li>
            <li><strong>LLM Research:</strong> Developing efficient Mixture-of-Experts architectures</li>
            <li><strong>EU Projects:</strong> Contributing to Horizon Europe cybersecurity initiatives</li>
            <li><strong>Open Source:</strong> Python libraries for NLP and social media analysis</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Research Keywords -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Research Keywords</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          {["Artificial Intelligence", "Machine Learning", "Natural Language Processing", "Large Language Models", "Deep Learning", "Cybersecurity", "Social Media Analysis", "Bot Detection", "Greece", "Technical University Crete", "Parasecurity Group", "Python", "PyTorch", "Transformers"].map(keyword => (
            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-blue-100 dark:bg-blue-900 text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-200 text-sm rounded-full">
              {keyword}
            </span>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

    </section>

    <!-- FIXED: Research Project Schema (No Validation Errors) -->
